other_tests.findings: Colorless, clear CSF; 217 total nucleated cells per mm3 (100% neutrophils); protein 39 mg/dl; glucose 67 mg/dl; Gram's stain showed abundant polymorphonuclear leukocytes, no organisms seen.
Positive for Neisseria meningitidis, Gram's stain revealed intracellular and extracellular gram-negative diplococci.
